# Release Workflow

## Version Source of Truth
`ha-raumkernel-addon/config.yaml` is the **master version file**.

## Correct Steps for a New Version

### 1. Edit code in `ha-raumkernel-addon/rootfs/app/`
All runtime JS lives here. **Never edit the copies in `custom_components/` or
`ha-raumkernel-addon/teufel_raumfeld_raumkernel/` directly** — they are generated.

### 2. Bump version in config.yaml
```yaml
version: "1.X.Y"
```

### 3. Run prepare-build.sh (ALWAYS — never skip)
```bash
cd /home/holli/BUILD/ha-raumkernel/ha-raumkernel-addon && bash prepare-build.sh
```
This script does **all** of the following in one shot:
- Runs `sync-version.sh` → updates `rootfs/app/package.json`, `package-lock.json`, `custom_components/.../manifest.json`
- Copies `rootfs/app/RaumkernelHelper.js` → `custom_components/teufel_raumfeld_raumkernel/`
- Copies `rootfs/app/tunein-patch.cjs`    → `custom_components/teufel_raumfeld_raumkernel/`
- Copies the entire `custom_components/teufel_raumfeld_raumkernel/` tree → `ha-raumkernel-addon/teufel_raumfeld_raumkernel/` (the Docker COPY source)
- Removes `config.yaml` from the bundle (prevents "dockerfile is missing")

### 4. Update CHANGELOG.md
Add a `## 1.X.Y` entry at the top of `ha-raumkernel-addon/CHANGELOG.md`.

### 5. Commit ALL changed files, then push
```bash
cd /home/holli/BUILD/ha-raumkernel
git add -A
git commit -m "v1.X.Y: <short description>"
git push
```

## Files that must all show the same version after a release
| File | Updated by |
|------|-----------|
| `ha-raumkernel-addon/config.yaml` | manual |
| `ha-raumkernel-addon/rootfs/app/package.json` | `sync-version.sh` (via prepare-build) |
| `ha-raumkernel-addon/rootfs/app/package-lock.json` | `npm install --package-lock-only` (via prepare-build) |
| `custom_components/teufel_raumfeld_raumkernel/manifest.json` | `sync-version.sh` (via prepare-build) |
| `ha-raumkernel-addon/teufel_raumfeld_raumkernel/manifest.json` | `cp -r` in prepare-build |

## JS files that must stay in sync across three locations
| Source (edit here) | Destinations (generated by prepare-build) |
|--------------------|------------------------------------------|
| `ha-raumkernel-addon/rootfs/app/RaumkernelHelper.js` | `custom_components/teufel_raumfeld_raumkernel/RaumkernelHelper.js` → `ha-raumkernel-addon/teufel_raumfeld_raumkernel/RaumkernelHelper.js` |
| `ha-raumkernel-addon/rootfs/app/tunein-patch.cjs` | `custom_components/teufel_raumfeld_raumkernel/tunein-patch.cjs` → `ha-raumkernel-addon/teufel_raumfeld_raumkernel/tunein-patch.cjs` |

If you skip prepare-build.sh:
- The bundled `/integration` inside Docker still carries the old JS → `IntegrationManager`
  sees bundled==installed version → logs "Integration already up to date" → no HA restart
  notification → users never pick up JS fixes.

## ⚠️ Never put config.yaml inside ha-raumkernel-addon/teufel_raumfeld_raumkernel/
HA Supervisor scans recursively for `config.yaml`. If one exists in the bundle with
the addon slug, Supervisor treats it as a second (no-Dockerfile) addon →
"dockerfile is missing" on every update.
`prepare-build.sh` removes it automatically. Never restore it.
